      "writtenOn": "2018-12-03T18:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Part of me likes our system with all GrVkResources are gotten via calls to GrVkResourceProvider. To keep consistency with the rest of the system maybe we have these calls on GrVkResourceProvider instead. The resource provider can then ask the GrVkGpu for the current GrVkCommandPool. Since it makes sense for the command pool to own the caches of command buffers, I think the resource provider would then just call these functions on the command pool. I think it would even be fine for the command pool to make these private and friend the resource provider.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 42,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 44,
        "endChar": 81
      },
      "revId": "f41619de18ee72cc5146a15ca1fda762919de3f4",
